quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  11,46,"He said, “O Noah, he is not of your family; surely, it is an unrighteous deed{1}, so do not{2}ask Me about something you know nothing about; I surely admonish you lest you be one of the ignorant.”",footnotes:1:[Qira’at: Al-Kesa’i and Ya’qub read it as: “…surely, he acted unrighteously,”],footnotes:2:[Qira’at: Nafie’, Ibn Kathir, Ibn Amer and Abu Ja’far read it as: “…so never ask me about…”]
  11,47,"He said, “O My Lord, I do seek refuge with You from asking You about what I have no knowledge of, and unless You forgive me and have mercy on me, I will be one of the losers.”"
  11,48,"It was said, “O Noah, disembark with peace from Us, and with blessings upon you and upon communities that will spring from those with you. And to<i>(other) </i>communities We shall grant enjoyment, then a painful punishment from Us will touch them.”"
  11,49,"That is of the stories of the hidden realm which we reveal to you<sup>sg </sup>; never were you nor your people to know them before this, so be patient; the future outcome surely belongs to the people who are mindful<i>(of God) </i>."
  11,50,"And to ʻĀd, their brother Hud. He said, “O my people, worship Allah; you have no other god but Him; you are nothing but fabricators."
  11,51,"O my people, I ask you no reward for it; my reward is only from the One Who originated me. Do you not reason?"
  11,52,"And, O my people, ask forgiveness from your Lord then repent to Him. He will send down abundant rain from the sky for you and will add strength to your strength. But do not turn away as criminals.”"
  11,53,"They said, “O Hud, you did not come to us with any evident proof, and we shall not abandon our gods for your words, and we shall not believe in you."
